programme.desc: Cynical, hard-drinking teacher Elizabeth Halsey hates her job and the kids in her class, and hopes to escape her daily grind by landing a rich husband. A wealthy substitute seems like a suitable candidate, but she has a rival for his attention in a squeaky-clean colleague. Comedy, starring Cameron Diaz, Justin Timberlake, Jason Segel and Lucy Punch.

programme.title: Pitch Perfect
programme.desc: A new student finds herself a social outcast during her first year of college, but soon acquires a new circle of friends in a band of misfits with a shared talent for singing. She joins their a cappella group and leads them to compete in the campus music competitions. Comedy, starring Anna Kendrick, Rebel Wilson and Elizabeth Banks.

programme.title: The Female Brain
programme.desc: When a scientist studies the differences between the male and female brain, her findings dictate how she lives her life. Comedy directed by and starring 2 Broke Girls creator Whitney Cummings, with Sofia Vergara and Toby Kebbell.

programme.title: Summer Rental
programme.desc: An overworked air traffic controller plans to get away from it all by taking his family to Florida. A succession of mishaps threaten their planned peaceful break, as the stressed family man gets drawn into a bitter feud with a pompous local sailing champion. Comedy, starring John Candy, Richard Crenna, Karen Austin and Rip Torn.

programme.title: Napoleon Dynamite
programme.desc: A socially inept high-school student and his lonely unemployed brother find their eccentric home life thrown into upheaval when their meddling uncle comes to stay. The teenage oddball tries to make the best of his changing circumstances, while putting all his skills to the task of helping his new best friend win the class presidency. Comedy, starring Jon Heder, Efren Ramirez and Haylie Duff.

programme.title: Fun with Dick and Jane
programme.desc: A highly paid executive loses everything after his corrupt boss's false accounting ruins the firm and leaves him to take the blame. Flat-broke and with no income or savings to maintain his lavish lifestyle, he and his wife decide the only way to support themselves is to turn to crime. Remake of the 1976 comedy, with Jim Carrey, Tea Leoni, Alec Baldwin and Richard Jenkins.

programme.title: Mamma Mia
programme.desc: A former member of a singing trio, now running a hotel on a Greek island, is reunited with her old bandmates for her daughter's wedding - but is surprised when three of her old flames also show up unexpectedly. The three men have been invited by the bride, who wants to find out which one of them is her father. Musical comedy, with a soundtrack of Abba songs, starring Meryl Streep, Pierce Brosnan, Julie Walters, Colin Firth, Stellan Skarsgard and Amanda Seyfried.

programme.title: Step Brothers
programme.desc: Brennan and Dale are two 40-year-old men who have never flown the nest. All that changes when Brennan's mother marries Dale's father, and the spoiled sons are forced to share a room. They take an instant dislike to each other, but when their long-suffering parents finally insist they find jobs, they learn to work together. Comedy, with Will Ferrell, John C Reilly, Mary Steenburgen and Richard Jenkins.

programme.title: Pretty Woman
programme.desc: A ruthless millionaire hires a prostitute while on a business trip. Realising she may be useful in helping him keep up a successful appearance, he pays her to accompany him for a week as he associates with the rich and powerful - but falls in love despite their many differences. Romantic comedy, starring Richard Gere and Julia Roberts, with Ralph Bellamy and Laura San Giacomo.

programme.title: Beetlejuice
programme.desc: Recently deceased couple Adam and Barbara Maitland enlist the professional services of a hard-boiled veteran ghost to scare away the obnoxious yuppie family who have moved into their former home. Tim Burton's supernatural comedy, starring Michael Keaton, Geena Davis, Alec Baldwin, Winona Ryder, Jeffrey Jones and Catherine O'Hara.

Comedy, starring Sacha Baron Cohen, Michael Gambon, Charles Dance, Kellie Bright, Martin Freeman and Rhona Mitra.

programme.desc: A professional relationship guru, who specialises in offering advice to lonely single men, helps an unlucky-in-love accountant to woo the girl of his dreams. However, when he finds himself falling for a beautiful gossip columnist, his usual charm abandons him and he discovers his expertise counts for nothing. Romantic comedy, with Will Smith, Eva Mendes, Kevin James, Amber Valletta, Julie Ann Emery, Adam Arkin and Michael Rapaport.

programme.title: Whisky Galore
programme.desc: Scottish islanders try to get their hands on the shipload of booze that washes up on their shores. Comedy, starring James Cosmo, Eddie Izzard and Naomi Battrick.

programme.title: The Little Hours
programme.desc: In the Middle Ages, three nuns at a countryside convent encounter a young gardener posing as a deaf-mute, and try to resist temptation. Comedy, starring Alison Brie, Dave Franco, Kate Micucci and Aubrey Plaza.

programme.title: Dear Dictator
programme.desc: A British-Caribbean dictator flees his island nation, and hides with a rebellious teenage girl in suburban America. There he teaches the youngster how to start a revolution and overthrow the `mean girls' at her high school. Comedy, starring Michael Caine, Odeya Rush and Katie Holmes.

programme.title: The Family Stone
programme.desc: New York career woman Meredith Morton struggles to make the right impression on her future in-laws when they meet her over Christmas. She decides to ask her younger sister to join her as moral support, but matters take a turn for the worse over dinner on Christmas Eve, when Meredith's attempts to win the hearts of her hosts only end up driving them - and her fiance Everett - further away. Festive comedy drama, starring Sarah Jessica Parker, Dermot Mulroney, Diane Keaton, Craig T Nelson and Claire Danes.

programme.title: She's Out of My League
programme.desc: Distinctly average and unimpressive Kirk cannot believe his luck when he lands a date with the clever and beautiful Molly. The pair embark on a relationship but Kirk's insecurities lead him to question whether they belong together. Romantic comedy, starring Jay Baruchel, Alice Eve, TJ Miller, Mike Vogel, Nate Torrence and Lindsay Sloane.

programme.title: American Pie
programme.desc: Four teenage boys make a solemn pact to lose their virginity before the high-school prom, and though their antics cause them huge embarrassment and public humiliation, the friends also learn about love and affection in their relations with the opposite sex. Coming-of-age comedy, starring Jason Biggs, Shannon Elizabeth, Chris Klein, Alyson Hannigan, Mena Suvari, Seann William Scott and Eugene Levy.

programme.title: Bruce Almighty
programme.desc: God tires of a down-on-his-luck reporter's constant complaining, so passes on His powers to give him a taste of ultimate responsibility. The newsman falls in love with his extraordinary abilities - but a never-ending stream of incoming prayers and his ambitious attempt to please everyone soon prove there is more to the job than meets the eye. Comedy, starring Jim Carrey, Jennifer Aniston and Morgan Freeman.

Disney animation, with the voices of Tom Hulce, Demi Moore and Kevin Kline.

Thriller, starring Denzel Washington, Angelina Jolie, Michael Rooker, Mike McGlone, Luis Guzman and Queen Latifah.

As they flee for their lives, the interrogator has to contend with not only the enemies hunting them, but also the mind games of his prisoner. Thriller, with Denzel Washington and Ryan Reynolds.

Action thriller, the final film from director Tony Scott, starring Denzel Washington, Chris Pine and Rosario Dawson.

Thriller, written and directed by Peaky Blinders creator Steven Knight, starring Matthew McConaughey, Anne Hathaway and Diane Lane.

Starring Jake Gyllenhaal, Robert Downey Jr, Mark Ruffalo and Brian Cox.

Thriller, starring Jodie Foster, Peter Sarsgaard, Sean Bean and Greta Scacchi.

Crime caper sequel, starring George Clooney, Brad Pitt, Julia Roberts, Catherine Zeta-Jones, Matt Damon, Andy Garcia and Don Cheadle.

He plans a scheme that will leave Bank penniless, but needs the help of an old enemy. Comedy crime caper sequel, with George Clooney, Al Pacino, Brad Pitt, Matt Damon, Andy Garcia and Elliott Gould.

He focuses on one victim in particular, a woman whom he believes holds the key to the crime, and becomes convinced that he can prevent the explosion ever happening. Sci-fi thriller, with Denzel Washington, Paula Patton, Val Kilmer and Jim Caviezel.

In the search for his true identity, he is pursued by assassins - but his skill at evading them suggests his own past is far from straightforward. Thriller, starring Matt Damon, Franka Potente, Chris Cooper, Clive Owen and Brian Cox.

Action thriller sequel, starring Matt Damon, Brian Cox, Joan Allen and Julia Stiles.

programme.title: The Big Split
programme.desc: It's an action-packed week for President Trump on two fronts, creating a split-screen effect for the American people. On one hand, the President travels to Vietnam to meet with Kim Jong Un of North Korea, and have a big moment on the world stage. On the other hand, the President's personal attorney, Michael Cohen, testifies before Congress about potential presidential dirt he may have. Emily Jane Fox, a reporter for Vanity Fair who has been following Cohen, joins the hosts this week to help cover the hearings.(c)

programme.title: Patriots Day
programme.desc: In the aftermath of the Boston Marathon bombing, Police Sergeant Tommy Saunders (Mark Wahlberg) joins courageous survivors, first responders and investigators in a race against the clock to hunt down the bombers before they strike again. The stories of Special Agent Richard Deslauriers (Kevin Bacon), Police Commissioner Ed Davis (John Goodman), Sergeant Jeffrey Pugliese (J.K. Simmons) and nurse Carol Saunders (Michelle Monaghan) are all woven together to show the strength of the city.

programme.title: The Foreigner
programme.desc: A humble London businessman's (Jackie Chan), long-buried past erupts in a revenge-fueled vendetta when the only person left for him to love - his teenage daughter - is taken from him in a senseless act of politically-motivated terrorism. In his relentless search for the identity of the terrorists, he is forced into a cat-and-mouse conflict with a British government official (Pierce Brosnan) whose own past may hold clues to the identities of the elusive killers.

programme.title: Pilot
programme.desc: Chuck Rhoades, a powerful U.S. Attorney for the Southern District of New York, is tipped to a case of insider trading with links to billionaire hedge fund king Bobby "Axe" Axelrod. While it could be a career-defining case for Chuck, he must tread carefully, because his wife, Wendy, is the in-house performance coach at Axe Capital and Axe's key confidante. But a costly purchase by Axe gives Chuck the opening he needs, setting off a cat and mouse game where the stakes are high and intensely personal. Series premiere.(c)

programme.title: Naming Rights
programme.desc: Axe installs rigorous compliance measures to gird the company against the US Attorney's office investigation. When Wendy questions Axe's methods, he compels her to prove her loyalty. Chuck's probe is temporarily derailed when he has to divert resources to a case against an Axe rival, billionaire Steven Birch. Hall, Axe's fixer, develops a mole inside the US Attorney's office, while Axe makes an aggressive move under the guise of a charitable contribution in order to settle an old score.(c)

programme.title: YumTime
programme.desc: Chuck discovers that while he pursued Steven Birch, the rival Eastern District has made inroads in the Axe case and that he needs to get it back. Axe makes an activist play for a family owned bakery corporation - a move reverberates back to Chuck by way of a very personal connection. Meanwhile, Wendy is thrown into a moral dilemma during a confidential session. And Lara Axelrod tries to protect her husband's reputation from a potentially damaging "tell all" book.(c)

programme.title: Short Squeeze
programme.desc: Axe takes a spontaneous trip to see Metallica with his childhood friends and meets a woman who makes him face the limits of his own freedom. He also must fend off a short squeeze - an attack on one of his important holdings - led by Chuck's father. Back in New York, Chuck learns about the inner workings of Axe Capital, but he must also take action against his father for stock manipulation. Plus, Axe reckons with a betrayal and upon his return makes a momentous decision about the direction of his firm.(c)

programme.title: The Good Life
programme.desc: Axe orders his traders to unload their positions, and he unceremoniously disappears from Axe Capital. As Axe questions his life choices and plans a trip on his new yacht, Wags and Wendy struggle to maintain morale and order amid the chaos. Meanwhile, Chuck intensifies his investigation in response to Axe's disappearance and is led to a farm in Iowa, where he discovers a key witness to a questionable trade. Armed with the damning evidence, Chuck sends the FBI into Axe Capital to make a surprising arrest.(c)

programme.title: The Deal
programme.desc: Axe plans a scorched-earth defense against the public attack on his company - threatening his relationship with Wendy in the process. programme.desc: In the early 1980s, after his recent and high profile defeat to Larry Holmes, boxing legend Muhammad Ali takes it upon himself to talk a suicidal stranger down from a ledge. Using his unique brand of wit and wisdom, he succeeds in persuading the man that life is worth living, and learns a huge amount about himself in the process. Starring Noel Clarke as Muhammad Ali, Osy Ikhile as Joe, Lucian Msamati as Herbert Muhammad and Danny John-Jules as Don King.

programme.title: Friday Night Lights
programme.desc: Based on H.G. Bissinger's book, which profiled the economically depressed town of Odessa, Texas and their heroic high school football team, The Permian High Panthers.

programme.title: Equilibrium

Angus MacFadyen, Emily Watson, Taye Diggs and Sean Bean costar in this thoughtful, fast-paced blend of "The Matrix" and George Orwell's "1984.".

programme.title: Bull Durham
programme.desc: A baseball groupie who has an affair with one minor-league baseball player each season meets an up-and-coming pitcher and the experienced catcher assigned to him.

programme.title: High Plains Drifter
programme.desc: A nameless stranger (Clint Eastwood) rides into a small town and immediately kills three gunmen. Impressed by his abilities, the townsfolk hire him to protect the town from three outlaws about to be released from prison. However, the townsfolk begin to second-guess their hire when the nameless man begins to take advantage of them in exchange for providing protection. Directed by and Starring Clint Eastwood.

programme.title: Jackie Brown
programme.desc: A cash smuggling stewardess gets pressure from the cops to help bring down her crime boss, and comes up with a plan to double cross both sides. Directed by Quentin Tarantino. Starring Pam Grier, Samuel L. Jackson, and Robert Foster.

programme.title: Inglourious Basterds
programme.desc: A squadron of vengeful, Nazi-killing Allied soldiers becomes embroiled in a plot to firebomb a Parisian movie theater hosting a film premiere that Adolf Hitler plans to attend in this comically violent World War II action smash starring Brad Pitt, Diane Kruger and Oscar® winner Christoph Waltz.

programme.title: American Pie
programme.desc: Four high school friends navigate through their sexually frustrating senior year as they strive for the most eagerly anticipated rite of adulthood: losing one's virginity.

programme.title: American Pie 2
programme.desc: After a year apart - attending different schools, meeting different people - a group of friends rent a beach house and vow to have the best summer ever.

programme.title: American Wedding
programme.desc: Jason Biggs and Alyson Hannigan star in this sequel to the classic American Pie comedies - as a couple of high-school sweethearts who need to get married in a hurry, before the groom's grandmother kicks the bucket. Also stars January Jones and Eugene Levy.

programme.title: Tone Bell: Can't Cancel This
programme.desc: Comedian Tone Bell simply wants to live in a world where Alaska is cold, student loans are paid and jelly is free. He's finally found the one place his uncompromising view of this unfair world can't be stopped.

programme.desc: The life of boxer Jake LaMotta (Robert De Niro), as the violence and temper that leads him to the top in the ring destroys his life outside of it. Directed by Martin Scorsese.

programme.desc: An already bad day for Driver is not getting any better. He makes a big haul of millions that would give him a nice summer vacation on easy street, but it goes south - literally. During a high-speed car chase with the US Border Patrol and a bleeding body in his back seat, Driver flips his car smashing through the border wall, tumbling violently, coming to a stop in Mexico. Apprehended by the Mexican authorities, he is sent to a hard-core prison where he enters the strange and dangerous world of "El Pueblito". Starring Mel Gibson.

programme.desc: A New York businessman seeks vengeance against society's criminal underworld for the death of his wife and the rape of his daughter.(n)

programme.desc: Kate Hudson and Matthew McConaughey star in this hit romantic comedy about a magazine writer assigned to seduce and then alienate the perfect man in just ten days - a task that proves more difficult when the guy she picks turns out to be the perfect man...for her. However, Mr. Right is also operating from a career-related secret agenda. Bebe Neuwirth, Michael Michele, Robert Klein, Adam Goldberg and Shalom Harlow costar in this funny film from director Donald Petrie ("Welcome to Mooseport").

programme.title: The Back-Up Plan
programme.desc: Giving up on ever meeting Mr. Right, a single New York pet shop owner (Jennifer Lopez) chooses to have a baby via artificial insemination. On the very day she becomes pregnant, however, she bumps headlong into the man of her dreams (Alex O'Loughlin), who's available and highly interested. Will an impending child scuttle a dream-come-true love affair? Eric Christian Olsen costars in this romantic comedy.

programme.title: The Kite Runner
programme.desc: The best-selling novel by Khaled Hosseini becomes this heartbreaking drama about two boys in 1970's Afghanistan, best friends who are ripped apart by a tragic incident that haunts the rest of their lives. Decades later, one of them gets a chance for redemption, but it will mean a return to his ravaged homeland, now controlled by the brutal Taliban. Director Marc Forster ("Finding Neverland") and writer David Benioff ("Troy") crafted this heartfelt, poignant adaptation.

programme.title: Kepler's Dream
programme.desc: A young girl searches for a rare book that is missing from her grandmother's collection and tries to understand why her family is fractured.

programme.title: Jurassic School
programme.desc: Nerdy middle schooler Tommy is forced take care of a baby dinosaur after his cloned science fair project hatches early. He quickly begins to think of the creature not only as a pet, but also as a friend. But when the dinosaur escapes on the day of the fair, Tommy must figure out a way to get the creature back before greedy grown-ups get to him first.

programme.title: Love Means Zero
programme.desc: At 85 years old, Nick Bollettieri is a living legend. At his tennis academy in Florida, he raised a generation of champions. Courier. Seles. Agassi. No other coach has matched his success, his dominance or his fame. His greatness, though, came at a terrible price - broken marriages, financial ruin and a fractured relationship with his surrogate son and most cherished student, Andre Agassi. This documentary tells his story and explores the cost of his all-consuming drive for greatness. Directed and produced by Jason Kohn.

Rebecca has no desire to date despite efforts by her feisty neighbor, Olive, who has a love advice column called Call Me Cupid. When Olive is pressured by her editor to get with the times, she enlists Justin to help her answer a letter. Unbeknownst to Justin, she publishes his advice under the alter ego, Cupid's Proxy.

programme.title: Honey, I Blew Up The Kid
programme.desc: Wacky inventor Wayne Szalinski (Rick Moranis) accidentally zaps his two-and-a-half-year-old son with a particle beam, causing the child to grow whenever coming in contact with electricity. Soon topping 112 feet, the overgrown baby is attracted to the bright, shiny lights of Las Vegas, and nothing stands in his way.

programme.title: Show Dogs

programme.title: The Beaver

Gilby's luck seems to change when he meets Rachel (Odette Annable), the very thing Gilby needs to get his life back on track. Desperate to impress her, Gilby starts to weave a web of lies; one bigger than the next. Now in a sticky mess, Gilby is forced to face the uncomfortable truth about himself.

programme.title: Włatcy móch 2 (odc. 15)
programme.desc: Pełne odważnego humoru perypetie czterech ośmiolatków z klasy II b. Najmądrzejszy z całej paczki Konieczko jest zdeklarowanym ateistą. Dzięki swojej inteligencji zamierza przejąć kiedyś władzę nad światem. Póki co wiedza przeszkadza mu w codziennej komunikacji z otoczeniem. Anusiak odznacza się największym brakiem kultury i jest najsilniejszy wśród kolegów. Jest synem chłopa i planuje kiedyś założyć związek zawodowy. Najbogatszy i najsprytniejszy Maślana to kapitalista, który jest przekonany, że wszystko można kupić. Zombie Czesio, w którym za życia skumulowały się liczne wady rozwojowe i genetyczne, marzy o tym, by zostać piosenkarzem. W przeciwieństwie do swoich kumpli jest miły i życzliwy. Cała czwórka nieustannie naraża się swojej nauczycielce, surowej pani Frał. Niesforne łobuzy często też dokuczają koleżance z klasy, Andżelice, która przeprowadziła się z rodzicami do Polski ze Stanów. Odważna i wygadana dziewczynka w przyszłości planuje bogato wyjść za mąż.

programme.title: Włatcy móch 2 (odc. 19)
programme.desc: Pełne odważnego humoru perypetie czterech ośmiolatków z klasy II b. Najmądrzejszy z całej paczki Konieczko jest zdeklarowanym ateistą. Dzięki swojej inteligencji zamierza przejąć kiedyś władzę nad światem. Póki co wiedza przeszkadza mu w codziennej komunikacji z otoczeniem. Anusiak odznacza się największym brakiem kultury i jest najsilniejszy wśród kolegów. Jest synem chłopa i planuje kiedyś założyć związek zawodowy. Najbogatszy i najsprytniejszy Maślana to kapitalista, który jest przekonany, że wszystko można kupić. Zombie Czesio, w którym za życia skumulowały się liczne wady rozwojowe i genetyczne, marzy o tym, by zostać piosenkarzem. W przeciwieństwie do swoich kumpli jest miły i życzliwy. Cała czwórka nieustannie naraża się swojej nauczycielce, surowej pani Frał. Niesforne łobuzy często też dokuczają koleżance z klasy, Andżelice, która przeprowadziła się z rodzicami do Polski ze Stanów. Odważna i wygadana dziewczynka w przyszłości planuje bogato wyjść za mąż.(n)
